<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  macOS privacy usage descriptions. Tauri v2 merges this file into the
  generated app bundle's Info.plist on macOS builds.

  These strings are MANDATORY for media capture, not just nice-to-have:

    - Without NSCameraUsageDescription, WKWebView strips the entire
      MediaDevices API — `navigator.mediaDevices` is `undefined`, so the
      camera-preview / device-picker enumerateDevices() + getUserMedia()
      calls throw before they can even prompt. (This was the "Camera
      unavailable: undefined is not an object" bug on Apple Silicon.)

    - Without NSMicrophoneUsageDescription, the FFmpeg AVFoundation
      microphone subprocess (audio/platform/ffmpeg_unix.rs) is denied by
      TCC and captures no samples, since it inherits the app's TCC
      identity and that identity has declared no mic intent.

  The text is shown verbatim in the macOS permission prompt — keep it
  plain-language and specific to what the user is about to do.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>NSCameraUsageDescription</key>
	<string>Doove uses your camera to record a presenter video alongside your screen recordings.</string>
	<key>NSMicrophoneUsageDescription</key>
	<string>Doove uses your microphone to record narration alongside your screen recordings.</string>
</dict>
</plist>
